			<item>
				<title>Scheduler, and KV transfer in disaggregated prefill</title>
				<link>https://zhixuan-zxli.github.io/llm/scheduler/</link>
				<pubDate>Sat, 06 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid>https://zhixuan-zxli.github.io/llm/scheduler/</guid>
				<description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;1-scheduler&#34;&gt;1. Scheduler&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;Scheduler&lt;/code&gt; (&lt;code&gt;vllm/v1/core/sched/scheduler.py&lt;/code&gt;) is the central resource allocator for vLLM&amp;rsquo;s v1 engine. Each iteration it decides which requests run, how many tokens each gets, and which KV cache blocks to (re-)use. It owns two queues — &lt;code&gt;self.waiting&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;self.running&lt;/code&gt; — plus a &lt;code&gt;KVCacheManager&lt;/code&gt; for block allocation and an optional &lt;code&gt;KVConnectorBase_V1&lt;/code&gt; for cross-node KV transfer. The scheduler has no notion of a distinct &amp;ldquo;prefill phase&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;decode phase&amp;rdquo;; every request is simply tracked by &lt;code&gt;num_computed_tokens&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;num_tokens_with_spec&lt;/code&gt;, and the scheduler&amp;rsquo;s job is to close the gap between them.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
